===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|s}}

# Something that happens to someone by [[chance]], a chance occurrence, especially a favourable one.
#: {{ux|en|The raffle is just a matter of '''luck'''.}}
#: {{ux|en|Sometimes it takes a bit of '''luck''' to get success.}}
#: {{ux|en|I couldn't believe my '''luck''' when I found a fifty dollar bill on the street.}}
#: {{ux|en|Gilbert had some bad '''luck''' yesterday — he got pick-pocketed and lost fifty dollars.}}
# A superstitious feeling that brings [[fortune]] or [[success]].
#: {{ux|en|He blew on the dice for '''luck'''.}}
#: {{ux|en|I wish you lots of '''luck''' for the exam tomorrow.}}
# [[success|Success]].
#: {{ux|en|I tried for ages to find a pair of blue suede shoes, but didn't have any '''luck'''.}}
#: {{ux|en|He has a lot of '''luck''' with the ladies, perhaps it is because of his new motorbike.}}
# {{lb|en|video games|computing}} The results of a {{l|en|random number generator}}.
#: {{ux|en|The creators of {{w|tool-assisted speedrun|tool-assisted speedruns}} often manipulate a lot of '''luck''' to get the most favorable results in order to save the most time.}}

